The paper deals with the problem of online path planning for UAVs with on-board sensors for joint detection and tracking of multiple unknown radio-tagged objects. This problem is relevant to the field of robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves developing algorithms for autonomous decision-making. The paper also involves signal processing techniques for transforming raw signals into the time-frequency domain, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of accommodating maneuvering objects capable of switching between different dynamic modes, which is relevant to the field of control systems (cs.SY).
